<DOCNO> AP881213-0009 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-12-13-88 2358EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Nicaragua-Attacks     12-13 0146</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Nicaragua-Attacks,0149</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two Reported Killed in Rebel Attacks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MANAGUA, Nicaragua (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Guerrillas ambushed a government truck
in central Nicaragua, killing one man and injuring another,
state-run Voice of Nicaragua reported.
   Also Tuesday, the official newspaper Barricada said a girl was
killed and three other civilians injured during a rebel attack on
Sunday.
   Rebels ambushed the Agriculture and Agrarian Reform Ministry
truck early Monday about 43 miles east of Managua in Chontales
province, the Voice of Nicaragua said. Barricada provided no details
on the attack in Puerto Esperanza, which is about 110 miles east of
Managua in Zelaya province.
   The U.S.-backed rebels, known as Contras, have waged a 7-year war
to topple the leftist Sandinista government. The Contras and
Sandinistas signed a cease-fire agreement in March, but talks on a
definitive truce broke down in September.
   Each side accuses the other of frequent cease-fire violations.
</TEXT>
