<FILEID>AP-NR-12-13-88 0650EST</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>u i PM-NewOrleansBishop     12-13 0105</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-New Orleans Bishop,0105</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Pope Names Wheeling-Charleston Bishop New Archbishop of New Orleans</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pope John Paul II today accepted the
resignation for reasons of age of Archbishop Philip M. Hannan of New
Orleans, the Vatican announced.
   The pope appointed the bishop of Wheeling-Charleston, W.Va.,
Monsignor Francis B. Schulte, to succeed Hannan in New Orleans, the
Vatican said.
   Hannan, who hosted the pope when he visited New Orleans during a
U.S. pilgrimage last year, on May 20 turned 75, the age at which
bishops must submit their resignations.
   Schulte, 61, born in Philadelphia, has been serving as
Wheeling-Charleston bishop since 1985.
</TEXT>
