<2ND_LINE>PM-Pit Bull Attack,0254</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Pit Bull Kills 6-Month-Old Girl</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CANTON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 6-month-old girl was fatally mauled by a
pit bull that a witness said was apparently after a cookie the baby
was holding.
   ``It was awful,'' said Helen Douglas, who lives in the apartment
next door to the girl's parents, Greg Vergara and Carrie Haverstock
Vergara.
   ``I was there, I saw it. I saw it every time I closed my eyes
last night,'' Ms. Douglas said Monday.
   The baby, Amber Haverstock, died Sunday night at Akron Children's
Hospital Medical Center, nearly five hours after the attack,
authorities said.
   Fire Department paramedic Tim O'Brien said the baby was badly
mauled. She had been bitten in the face and neck.
   ``There were bites over her entire body, especially the upper
torso,'' said O'Brien.
   Ms. Douglas said she and her brother, Robert Nieb, were in the
apartment next door when they heard the screams of the mother and
child, who were alone in their apartment with the family dog.
   ``We ran next door and ... my brother tried to get the baby and
the dog,'' she said. At least three attempts to rescue the baby were
unsuccessful, she said, and ``finally, he (the dog) just let her
go.''
   Police turned the dog, a 5-year-old male, over to the Stark
County Animal Control Department.
   ``I'll tell you one thing, that dog's never leaving here alive,''
department director Phil Palumbo said when he learned the child had
died.
</TEXT>
