<2ND_LINE>PM-Taxi Shootings, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0514,0308</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Two Cab Drivers Shot To Death, Third Wounded</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: New throughout to CORRECT times of shootings and CORRECT
injury of third driver to show he did not suffer gunshot wound.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>KILLEEN, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gunman shot to death two taxi drivers and
injured a third in a series of robbery attacks in Killeen and a
nearby Army base, police said.
   One of the Yellow Cab drivers was shot to death and another was
bitten on the hand and forehead in this central Texas town, while
the third was shot to death at nearby Fort Hood, police said.
   The incidents began Monday night and continued until early today,
said authorities, who did not immediately release names of the
victims.
   The assailant, who was described to police by the wounded driver,
called a taxi to take him from Killeen to the Army post. Inside the
post, the man robbed the driver and shot him to death.
   The man then called a Yellow Cab to take him from Fort Hood to
Killeen. He again robbed the driver and shot him to death on a
street in the central Texas town.
   A short time later, a third driver said a man attempted to rob
him and shot at him on a Killeen street.
   The driver grabbed the gunman's hand, forcing the bullet to go
out the car window and miss the driver, said a Yellow Cab dispatcher
in Killeen who would not identify himself. The gunman then bit the
driver on the hand and forehead, the dispatcher said.
   The driver was treated at a hospital and released, said James
Kelly, an investigator with the Killeen Police Department.
   Authorities say they do not know how much money was taken in the
robberies.
   State and military officers were investigating the shootings.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
