<2ND_LINE>PM-Mexico-Prison Fire,0187</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>20 Dead in Prison Fire</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By CAM ROSSIE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MONTERREY, Mexico (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fire broke out today in a ward at a
state penitentiary, killing 20 prisoners and injuring six, a state
official said.
   Raul Garza, state communications director, said the fire in a
ward at the Nuevo Leon state prison broke out about 3 a.m. when a
candle in a small altar to the Virgin of Guadalupe, Mexico's patron
saint, ignited a curtain.
   ``Yesterday (Monday) was a religious holiday to the Virgin of
Guadalupe so there were an inordinate amount of ... candles in the
dormitory to the virgin,'' Garza said in a telephone interview.
   He said the flames spread to curtains hanging from the four-level
bunk beds in the ward, which houses 116 prisoners.
   ``The mattresses also caught fire and there was a lot of smoke,''
Garza said. ``It was an accident.''
   He said the fire was brought under control about 30 minutes later
afetr it broke out and state authorities were investigating the
incident.
   The Nuevo Leon prison houses about 1,800 prisoners.
