<2ND_LINE>AM-Glamour Survey,0170</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Magazine Surveys Sex In The Workplace</HEAD>
<HEAD>Embargoed until 6 p.m. EST; Time set by source.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   More than 40 percent of the men surveyed by
Glamour magazine said they believe it is possible for a man to sleep
his way to the top in business, and 44 percent said they'd had an
affair with a female co-worker.
   The survey, in the January issue of Glamour, also found that
seven in 10 respondents have worked for a female boss, and nearly
one-quarter of them said they were sexually attracted to her.
   Only 6 percent had dated their female superiors, but half of the
respondents said they would feel comfortable in such a situation.
   Ninety percent of the men surveyed said they believe sexual
tension is a hindrance to productivity in the workplace.
   Glamour questioned 1,002 men by mail and in person. Although the
survey sought some demographic balance, the results are not
representative of the population at large, the magazine said.
</TEXT>
