<HEAD>Thomson Leaving as Head of Principals Group</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Scott Thomson, executive director of the
National Association of Secondary School Principals, said Tuesday he
will step down from his post at the end of 1989.
   Thomson, 58, has headed the nation's largest organization of
school administrators since 1980 and was its deputy executive
director for five years before that. He did not reveal future plans.
   A native of Oregon, Thomson is a former superintendent of the
Evanston Township High School District in Illinois. He was also
principal of Cubberley High School in California and once taught
social studies, math and English.
   The association has grown during his tenure from 33,500 to 41,000
principals, assistant principals and university professors.
