<DATELINE>HACKENSACK, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The wife of confrontational talk-show
host Morton Downey Jr. has filed a countersuit for divorce, claiming
he humiliated her.
   Kim Downey filed a lawsuit Monday in Superior Court in
Hackensack, saying her marriage of 10 years was an emotional ordeal
during which she was forced ``to remain submissive.''
   In an earlier divorce claim, Downey, an Englewood resident who is
host of a syndicated talk show from WWOR-TV in Secaucus, charged his
