meeting today at which they were expected to chart a course on money
policy for the next few weeks.
   Some analysts think they may tighten credit before the end of the
year if the economy shows signs of expanding too rapidly.
   In a new report today, the Commerce Department said retail sales
jumped 1.1 percent in November, following a revised 1.6 percent rise
