<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Mitsubishi     12-13 0153</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Mitsubishi,0161</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mitsubishi Corp. Posts 31.2 Percent Profit Gain In First Half Ended
Sept. 30</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Mitsubishi Corp., the largest Japanese trading
house, said Tuesday its consolidated profit rose 31.2 percent in the
first half of its fiscal year, reflecting healthy demand for its
steel products and higher prices for nonferrous metals.
   For the six months ended Sept. 30, Mitsubishi's net earnings
totaled 21.0 billion yen, or approximately $171 million, up from
16.0 billion yen a year earlier, the company said. Per share net
rose to 13.34 yen from 10.31 yen.
   Sales, or total trading transactions, rose 11.4 percent to 7.107
trillion yen, or $57.8 billion, from 6.377 trillion yen.
   The first-half results include returns from 100 full-line
consolidated subsidiaries.
   The yen figures were converted into dollars at a rate of 123 yen
to the dollar. The yen was actually somewhat weaker than that during
most of the reporting period.
</TEXT>
