<1ST_LINE>r f BC-ControlData     12-13 0180</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Control Data,0187</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Control Data To Sell Scientific Information Services Business</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BLOOMINGTON, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Control Data Corp. plans to sell its
Scientific Information Services business to Power Computing Co., the
companies said Tuesday.
   A sale price for the transaction, expected to be completed by the
end of this year, was not disclosed.
   The SIS business unit, based in Kansas City, markets timesharing
services to engineering, scientific and electric power utility
customers primarily in the United States. Under the terms of the
agreement, Power Computing will assume responsibility for all
customer contracts of SIS.
   Power Computing supplies computing services to the electric power
industry and to other engineering and financial service companies.
It is a unit of Babcock and Wilcox, a major operating unit of
McDermott International Inc.
   The company and its subsidiaries manufacture steam-generating
equipment, defense products, tubular products and process control
systems. They also provide engineering and construction services for
industrial and utility facilities onshore, and to the oil and gas
industry offshore.
   Control Data provides computer products and services to
scientific, engineering and business markets worldwide.
</TEXT>
