<HEAD>Three Senior Executives Elected to New Jobs at Tribune</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stanton R. Cook, president and chief executive
officer, will become chairman of Tribune Co., the media company
announced Tuesday.
   Cook's promotion was one of three front-office moves made by
company directors.
   Charles T. Brumback, 60, will become president and chief
operating officer of Tribune Co.
   John W. Madigan, 51, will become president and chief executive
officer of Chicago Tribune Co., which produces and distributes the
newspaper.
   Tribune Co. is a diversified media company engaged in newspaper
publishing, broadcasting, entertainment production and newsprint
manufacturing.
   It publishes the Chicago Tribune, the Orlando Sentinel and the
Daily News of New York, and operates WGN-TV.
   Cook, 63, will remain publisher of the Chicago Tribune.
   Brumback currently is president and chief executive officer of
Chicago Tribune Co., and Madigan is executive vice president of
Tribune Co.
   The appointments take effect Jan. 1.
